Sure, here's a simple JavaScript program that generates ASCII characters and their corresponding hex values from 0 to 127 (7F in hex).

```javascript
for(let i = 0; i <= 127; i++){
    console.log(`Hex: ${i.toString(16)}, ASCII: ${String.fromCharCode(i)}`);
}
```

This program uses a for loop to iterate over the numbers from 0 to 127. For each number, it converts the number to hex using the `toString` method with 16 as the radix. It also converts the number to its equivalent ASCII character using the `String.fromCharCode` method. Finally, it prints out both the hexadecimal and ASCII representations.

To run this program, you can paste it into a JavaScript environment such as your browser's console or a Node.js environment.
